<taxonomicName id="699CD2316A5DA4CBD5D95011ADEDDDD3" authority="Perkins, 1981" authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="1981" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Sphaerosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphaerosyllis magnidentata" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="magnidentata">Sphaerosyllis magnidentata Perkins, 1981</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C4029E74D86319A2DBC5080627A12EE8" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph id="F533545B202AC568124C528C1C8F3AE0" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="736DF2591390A7658A49B34FD7F9F653" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Questionable status. Reported from Greece by 
<bibRefCitation id="D2CE77A1DB3E61BFB2FAB813875C7A67" author="Koulouri, P." journalOrPublisher="Estuarine, Coastal and Shelf Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="392 - 407" title="A field experiment on trophic relations within the benthic boundary layer (BBL) over an oligotrophic continental shelf" volume="164" year="2015">Koulouri et al. (2015)</bibRefCitation>
, in the Mediterranean also known from Spain (
<bibRefCitation id="0398999B99B25D694D5310B9A5D1D855" author="Tena, Jose" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Marine Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="55 - 72" title="Polychaetes associated with different facies of the photophilic algal community in the Chafarinas archipelago (SW Mediterranean)" volume="67" year="2000">Tena et al. 2000</bibRefCitation>
), otherwise distributed in the Caribbean. The Mediterranean occurrence record leads to the inclusion of the species in the key of Mediterranean 
<taxonomicName id="16AD118F0C750357D8C1C744402E4892" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Sphaerosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphaerosyllis" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Sphaerosyllis</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="30F25CA41012966CFED0C1254F7F2FF7" author="Faulwetter, Sarah" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="327 - 345" title="Sphaerosyllislevantina sp. n. (Annelida) from the eastern Mediterranean, with notes on character variation in Sphaerosyllishystrix Claparede, 1863" volume="150" year="2011">Faulwetter et al. (2011b)</bibRefCitation>
, but the rarity of records indicates that it may in fact not be present in the region. A re-examination of the specimens is required to verify its presence in Greece and the Mediterranean.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
